      <h5>Design</h5>
      <h3>Onboarding</h3>
      <p>Focus: <span class="definition-badge">Understanding features</span></p>
      <p>The first time someone logs in is a critical moment. Our job is to help that person get to the ‘aha’ moment of understanding why this product deserves a spot in their life. Some pieces of the onboarding process were working ok, but we knew we could do better.</p>
      <p>To guide someone through their initial experience, we developed an onboarding 'happy path'. We then translated this happy path into an onboarding checklist.</p>
      <p>For example, if a new user shares their skills and interests, we can follow up with that person with volunteer opportunities that would be a perfect fit for them. This light weight investment of effort that could deliver long-term value. A perfect onboarding task.</p>
      <p>We also knew that people were most likely to come back to Bright Funds if they had used the product previously to support a nonprofit. Therefore, one of the checklist items was to find their first nonprofit to volunteer with or donate to. This action was higher effort, but was an important step in understanding the core product value.</p>
      <p>This checklist helps someone understand what they can do and celebrates early accomplishments along the way.</p>

    </div>

