      <h3>Tips and advice</h3>
      <p>Focus: <span class="definition-badge">Understanding features</span></p>
      <p>We knew that people weren’t fully aware of everything they could do on Bright Funds. Matching donations to fundraisers, setting up automatic donations, giving through payroll. These came up frequently through support conversations. </p>
      <p>Once someone did decide to use Bright Funds, we had opportunities to deliver personalized advice. Say you have $1,000 of matching and are giving $50 per month. Over the course of the year, you’ll be leaving $400 of matching on the table. If I wanted to use all of my matching, I would need to do the monthly calculations myself.</p>
      <p>Helping someone understand what they could do would help them take full advantage of their various benefits. Helping them make better decisions would deliver higher value.</p>
      <p>We worked through these two types of tips. Educational tips (What can I do) and contextual advice (What do you suggest).</p>
      <p>I looked at a few visual treatments for the educational tips. We wanted them to be prominent, but not get in the way. For example, we knew that if we periodically displayed a modal with tips people would likely close out that modal because it's interrupting the task they came in to do.</p>
      <p>Every user’s account has a home page. I decided to take over the header of this page with the tips. By doing so, the tips were prominent, they didn’t get in the way, and they take up additional screen real estate. </p>

      </div>

