      <h3>Goal setting</h3>
      <p>Focus: <span class="definition-badge">Frequency of usage</span></p>
      <p>Based on research from other fields (especially retirement saving) we were interested to see whether having someone set a goal for how much they’d like to give would result in them giving more or giving more often. </p>
      <p>The problem we were seeing was that many employees (let’s call her Rachel) would usually make one-time donations sporadically throughout the year. She donates when her company runs a giving or volunteer campaign, and then beyond that perhaps only when she’s asked by friends. At the same time, we heard that people like Rachel thought they should be giving more.</p>
      <p>Our hypothesis was that if we prompted people to set a goal for how much they'd like to give over the course of a year and then make it easy for her to follow up with her intentions, she would be more likely to give more and more often.</p>
      <p>Here's how we tested this feature: When Rachel logs in, she can set a goal. First, she selects which percentage of her salary she’d be interested in giving. We provide a benchmark of 6% based on research indicating that is how much people believe others should give.</p>

      </div>

